		<seg id="31">In short, even our &quot;moderate&quot; estimate may significantly underestimate the cost of America's involvement in Iraq.</seg>
		<seg id="32">And our estimate does not include any of the costs implied by the enormous loss of life and property in Iraq itself.</seg>
		<seg id="33">We do not attempt to explain whether the American people were deliberately misled regarding the war's costs, or whether the Bush administration's gross underestimate should be attributed to incompetence, as it vehemently argues is true in the case of weapons of mass destruction.</seg>
